emdash-guard bundles a checker script from a third party:

  scripts/check_em_dashes.py
    Source:  https://github.com/exmergo/skill-no-em-dashes
    License: MIT
    Copyright (c) the exmergo skill-no-em-dashes authors.

The script is vendored (copied in) so this plugin is self-contained: a Claude
Code plugin is copied to a cache directory on install and cannot read files
outside its own directory, so it cannot reference another plugin's copy.

Only the checker is third-party. The hook wiring (scripts/post_write_emdash.py,
hooks/hooks.json) is part of claude-guardrails.
